node.text:
In July 1947, 74 years ago, the Yakovlev Yak-23 made its first flight. The Yak-23 used a reverse engineered Rolls-Royce Derwent V engine and was exported to 5 nations who used it into the 60's. However, in Soviet service, it was replaced in the early 50's by the superior MiG-15.
_________________________________________

node.text:
In July 1945, 76 years ago, the Saab T 18B-2 made its first flight. The T 18B-2 appeared from the failed T 18B-1 project of carrying a torpedo. The T 18 B-2 was a modified T 18B-1 variant fitted with a 57 mm cannon in the nose, and was deployed to hunt naval targets.
